claim.claim-text:
12. A method of assessing the proficiency of a nucleic acid assay, said method comprising 
a) obtaining a test sample; 
b) preparing a nucleic acid reference standard comprising a target nucleic acid comprising a known nucleic acid sequence and a binding agent; 
c) assessing the presence or absence of a second nucleic acid in said test sample using a nucleic acid assay; and 
d) assessing the presence or absence of said known nucleic acid in said nucleic acid reference standard using the nucleic acid assay of (c), 
wherein detection of said known nucleic acid sequence in (d) is an indication that said nucleic acid assay is proficient.
